# Protos Web ‚Äî Cursor AI Rules
# =============================
# This file defines strict coding standards for Cursor AI assistant.
# All code generation MUST follow these rules without exception.

## Project Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router) with `src/` directory
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode, `allowJs: false` in `src/`)
- **Config**: `next.config.mjs` ‚Äî only root JS file (Next 14 does not support `next.config.ts`)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with CSS custom properties
- **Animations**: Framer Motion only ‚Äî GSAP is NOT installed
- **3D**: React Three Fiber (`@react-three/fiber`, `@react-three/drei`) ‚Äî NOT vanilla Three.js
- **Smooth Scroll**: `lenis` (via LenisProvider)
- **DOM + Canvas layers**: see `.cursor/rules/dom-canvas-layers.mdc` ‚Äî mandatory for any UI/3D work
- **i18n**: `next-intl` (5 locales: hr, en, de, it, es)
- **Icons**: `lucide-react` only (no Font Awesome, no icon CDN)
- **Loaders**: `ldrs` via `ProtosLoader` for inline/form loading ‚Äî **not** for boot screen
- **UI motion**: React Bits patterns live in `src/components/ui/` (`ShimmerText`, `GlowCard`, `MagneticButton`) ‚Äî see `docs/ui-motion-toolkit.md`
- **Backend**: Supabase (blog, contact, portfolio, edge functions; see `supabase/functions/README.md`)

## File Structure Rules
- All pages go in `src/app/[locale]/`
- All components go in `src/components/` with subdirs: `layout/`, `sections/`, `three/`, `ui/`, `providers/`, `admin/`, `legal/`, `seo/`, `navigation/`
- All lib/utils go in `src/lib/`
- All i18n messages go in `src/messages/{locale}.json`
- API routes go in `src/app/api/`

## Component Rules
1. **Always use `'use client'`** for components that use:
   - React hooks (useState, useEffect, useRef, etc.)
   - Framer Motion animations
   - Browser APIs (window, document, localStorage)
   - Three.js / R3F components
   - Event handlers

2. **Three.js components MUST**:
   - Use `@react-three/fiber` and `@react-three/drei` ‚Äî NEVER vanilla Three.js
   - Be dynamically imported with `next/dynamic` and `{ ssr: false }`
   - Be wrapped in `<Canvas>` from `@react-three/fiber`
   - Include `<Suspense>` fallback for loading states

3. **DOM + Canvas layers MUST** (full spec in `.cursor/rules/dom-canvas-layers.mdc`):
   - Site pages: `SiteBackground` ‚Üí `PageBackgroundCanvas` / per-route backgrounds in `three/backgrounds/` (fixed, behind)
   - Showcase: fullscreen Canvas; NO Header/Footer/SiteBackground (handled in `AppChrome`)
   - One showcase phase visible at a time (`loading` | `intro` | `playing`)
   - 3D objects in Canvas; never fake 3D with CSS transforms for showcase frames

4. **Framer Motion usage MUST**:
   - Use `whileInView` with `viewport={{ once: true }}` for scroll animations
   - Use `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit animations
   - Keep transition durations between 0.3s‚Äì0.8s for UI, up to 1.2s for hero elements

## Styling Rules
1. **Use Tailwind classes** as primary styling method
2. **CSS custom properties** (from globals.css) for theme colors:
   - `var(--primary)` = #ff6600
   - `var(--secondary)` = #8b5cf6
   - `var(--accent)` = #06b6d4
   - `var(--dark)` = #0a0a1a
   - `var(--dark-card)` = #0f0f2a
   - `var(--light)` = #e8e8f0
   - `var(--light-muted)` = #8888aa
3. **Gradients**: Use `var(--gradient-hero)` or Tailwind `bg-gradient-to-*` with CSS vars
4. **Border radius**: Use Tailwind rounded classes (rounded-xl, rounded-2xl, rounded-full)
5. **Dark theme only** ‚Äî do NOT add light mode styles

## Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `PageLoader.tsx`, `TransitionLink.tsx`)
- **Pages**: `page.tsx` inside route folders
- **Utilities/Hooks**: camelCase (e.g., `useScrollProgress.ts`)
- **CSS classes**: Tailwind utility-first, custom classes use kebab-case
- **i18n keys**: dot.notation (e.g., `nav.home`, `hero.title`)

## Performance Rules
1. **Dynamic imports** for heavy components (Three.js, charts, maps):
   ```tsx
   const HomeBackground = dynamic(() => import('@/components/three/backgrounds/HomeBackground'), {
     ssr: false,
     loading: () => <div className="w-full h-full bg-dark" />,
   })
   ```
2. **Image optimization**: Always use `next/image` with proper width/height/alt
3. **Font optimization**: Use `next/font/google` for Inter
4. **Lazy loading**: Use `loading="lazy"` for below-fold images
5. **Memoization**: Use `useMemo`/`useCallback` for expensive computations in R3F

## Backend Rules
- API routes in `src/app/api/` ‚Äî contact, blog, subscribe, admin (login/logout/session)
- Admin auth via `ADMIN_SECRET` on Vercel ‚Äî see `docs/security.md`
- Server actions in `src/actions/` ‚Äî Supabase reads/writes when env vars are set
- Supabase client in `src/lib/supabase.ts`
- Edge functions in `supabase/functions/` ‚Äî see `supabase/functions/README.md`
- Live schema managed via Supabase MCP/CLI ‚Äî see `supabase/migrations/README.md`
- **Public tech stack badges**: always read from `src/lib/tech-stacks.ts` ‚Äî never hardcode stack lists in i18n prose or components

## 3D Rules
- Before new 3D work: read `docs/3d-toolkit.md` and `.cursor/rules/r3f-drei-recipes.mdc`
- Use Context7 MCP for `@react-three/drei` / `@react-three/fiber` documentation

## i18n Rules
- Default locale: `hr` (Croatian)
- All user-facing text MUST use `useTranslations()` hook
- Translation keys go in all 5 locale files
- Route segments stay in Croatian (e.g., `/proces`, `/o-meni`, `/usluge`, `/kontakt`)
- Language selector must show all 5 languages with flag emojis

## Accessibility Rules
- All images must have `alt` text
- All buttons must have `aria-label` if no visible text
- All interactive elements must be keyboard-accessible
- Use semantic HTML (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`)
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA standards

## Git Rules
- Commit messages in English, imperative mood
- Prefix: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `style:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- One logical change per commit
- Never commit `node_modules/`, `.next/`, `.env`, `.env.local`

## FORBIDDEN
- ‚ùå Do NOT mix site chrome (Header/Footer/PageLoader/SiteBackground) into portfolio-showcase
- ‚ùå Do NOT stack multiple `fixed inset-0` overlays on showcase or site
- ‚ùå Do NOT use GSAP (not in stack) unless user explicitly adds it to package.json
- ‚ùå Do NOT use vanilla Three.js ‚Äî only React Three Fiber
- ‚ùå Do NOT use `pages/` router ‚Äî only App Router with `src/app/`
- ‚ùå Do NOT use CSS modules or styled-components ‚Äî only Tailwind + CSS vars
- ‚ùå Do NOT add light mode ‚Äî dark theme only
- ‚ùå Do NOT add new SQL migrations without coordinating with live remote schema
- ‚ùå Do NOT use `any` type ‚Äî always type properly
- ‚ùå Do NOT use inline styles unless absolutely necessary (use Tailwind)
- ‚ùå Do NOT create files outside the defined folder structure
- ‚ùå Do NOT remove existing working features when adding new ones
